cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper applies deep neural networks to predict long-term electricity demand, which is a typical task in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper uses stacked autoencoder and multilayer perceptrons, which are common neural network architectures, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category. Furthermore, the paper deals with data analysis and prediction, which suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible categories.
